passages.text: Japan | Business & Employment Services  TIMEE INC
Equity Research  August 28, 2025
Invite: Post Q3 Group Meeting with CFO Thur, 11 Sep 9PM JST (1PM\*BST, 8AM ET)

We are hosting a post results group meeting/Q&A session with Timee's CFO on Thursday, 11 Sep at 9:00PM JST/8:00PM HKT/2:00PM CET/1:00PM BST/8:00AM ET. Mr. Tomoaki Yagi will join us to discuss Q3 earnings and business outlook. The meeting will be conducted in Japanese with subsequent English translation from Ken Oiwa, the JEF analyst. For a Zoom link please contact Ken or your usual Jefferies sales contact.
- 9:00PM JST- 8:00PM HKT & SGT- 2:00PM CET- 1:00PM BST- 8:00AM ET
Jefferies Host: Ken Oiwa (Japan Equity Research Analyst)
- Mr. Tomoaki Yagi, CFO, Director at Timee, Inc.
Registration: Please contact your sales rep or Ken Oiwa's Team
Language: Japanese with English translation by Ken

Mr. Tomoaki Yagi Bio: Mr Yagi was engaged for six years in comprehensive trading, including commercial banking, trust banking and securities operations, and corporate sales (wholesale) operations at MUFG Bank. Following this, he was at investment bank operations, including IPOs for listed and unlisted companies, and M&A deals at the investment bank at Mitsubishi UFJ Morgan Stanley Securities. After overseeing business promotion and taking leadership in finance at SaaS Venture, he joined Timee in December 2020.

Our latest note on Timee, the leading spot work company, is here. Please get in touch with us or your Jefferies sales rep for the latest Excel model on Timee and Zoom link. Timee is set to release Q3 10/25 results on September 11, 2025 at 3:30PM JST.

Timee, Inc. operates a matching service for short term spot work for venues such as restaurants or distribution centers. The company is headed by a young CEO called Mr Ryo Ogawa who started this service while at University. This matching service has grown to be the number one spot work company in Japan. The benefit of spot work is flexibility when companies are struggling for workers. The clients are mainly restaurants or logistics or distribution centers. The benefits for restaurants are that it can fill a vacancy in a short period of time. As a market leader, Timee has workers review data after the shift. This is important as the workers do not require interviews or resume submission to get spot work. Therefore, the first few shifts are essentially interviews which makes the follow- up job offers likely or less likely. The right level of matching is essential. For example if there are too many registered workers to the number of premises, there will not be enough jobs where the registered workers get annoyed. Equally, if there are too many premises compared to registered workers, the premises run the risk of being understaffed. This can be the difference between not having a dishwasher available for a restaurant and the manager having to work this spot, which probably affects the day take for restaurants.

This is a high- growth stock, with the spot work market expected to grow by 5x from 2023 to 2028. We use PER for this valuation and at 25x FY10/26E. Downside risks include competition concerns, decrease in take rate and decrease in growth of the key sub segments. Upside risks are dividend payments, takeovers and revival of food and beverage sector.
(Article 3(1)e and Article 7 of MAR) Recommendation Publication Recommendation Distributed

Buy - Describes securities that we expect to provide a total return (price appreciation plus yield) of \(15\%\) or more within a 12- month period. Hold - Describes securities that we expect to provide a total return (price appreciation plus yield) of plus \(15\%\) or minus \(10\%\) within a 12- month period. Underperform - Describes securities that we expect to provide a total return (price appreciation plus yield) of minus \(10\%\) or less within a 12- month period. The expected total return (price appreciation plus yield) for Buy rated securities with an average security price consistently below \(10\) is \(20\%\) or more within a 12- month period as these companies are typically more volatile than the overall stock market. For Hold rated securities with an average security price consistently below \(10\) , the expected total return (price appreciation plus yield) is plus or minus \(20\%\) within a 12- month period. For Underperform rated securities with an average security price consistently below \(10\) , the expected total return (price appreciation plus yield) is minus \(20\%\) or less within a 12- month period.
NR - The investment rating and price target have been temporarily suspended. Such suspensions are in compliance with applicable regulations and/or Jefferies policies.
CS - Coverage Suspended. Jefferies has suspended coverage of this company.

NC - Not covered. Jefferies does not cover this company.
